What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's an overall decent course if you want to refine your skills in English in a relaxed setting. Good way to get into the swing of writing papers.
Tough but fun, I would highly recommend this class. But, bear in mind, it is a lot of work.
Definitely would. This is a great class for any incoming freshman concerned about their writing skills or simply want to polish them up. And Professor Fawcett is great!!

I think it definitely depends on who is teaching, and what the subject is. Because the subject material of this class wasn't very stimulating, I think it completely relied on the teacher to be interesting. As for other classes, I think the material was much more interesting.

I would recommend the class to a fellow student, and anyone who wants to improve their writing skills. It is an intensive writing seminar which requires a lot of work, but it pays off very well. I would especially recommend it to non-native English speakers. My English improved a lot through this course.
